  "text": "The spallation neutron experiments were carried out at Research Center for Nuclear Physics (RCNP) at Osaka University. To increase the number of upset FFs, stacked device under test (DUT) boards with four test chips are used. We measured SERs at four static conditions; (DATA, CLK) = (0, 1), (1, 1), (0, 0) and (1, 0). All measurement were done by initializing all FFs, and read data after five minutes. The neutron tests were carried out for two types of fabricated chips as shown in Fig. 10 . Acceleration factors of chip (a) and chip (b) measurement are 3.8 × 10 8 and 3.9 × 10 8 respectively compared with the sea level at NYC. Experimental results of the stacked FF are quoted from [CITATION_1] .",
